    "attributes": {
        "action": "Award H/B so rents paid in full to parents/sons/daughters over 18\r\nM/Severe ASD",
        "additional_details": "My son is now 20 years old and does not have full coherency. I have singular guardianship. He receives very little support and I receive the same 10 hrs. At the last meeting social services wanted to \r\ndrop those hours by a further 4. I cannot work because I am my sons \r\nfull time carer, meaning I am forced to remain on benefits. I have rent & bills to pay not to mention ensuring that their are hearty meals on the table for a growing lad. My housing benefit doesn't cut it do S/Fall's still \u00a3374 pm",
        "background": "No discrimination in H/Benefit.Rent for parents with children over 18 who have moderate to severe Autism Spectrum disorder should be paid in full as thousands of parents cannot work and are stuck on benefits due to lack of support as their young adult doesn't have the capacity to live independently.",
